{"review": [{"text_id": "SylESLC6Fr", "sid": 0, "sentence": "This paper studies the problem of learning from multiple tasks and additional noisy data."}, {"text_id": "SylESLC6Fr", "sid": 1, "sentence": "The proposed representation learning method first assigns each noisy data a relevance score using the topological information."}, {"text_id": "SylESLC6Fr", "sid": 2, "sentence": "Then the authors propose to minimize a combination of the loss of a class-prototype learning loss and a cosine classifier learning loss to learn a good representation generator g_theta."}, {"text_id": "SylESLC6Fr", "sid": 3, "sentence": "The empirical study validates the effectiveness of the proposed method."}, {"text_id": "SylESLC6Fr", "sid": 4, "sentence": "I have the following comments,"}, {"text_id": "SylESLC6Fr", "sid": 5, "sentence": "1. The studied problem that learning from few-shot data and large-scale noisy data is interesting. According to the experimental results, the proposed method seems to be promising."}, {"text_id": "SylESLC6Fr", "sid": 6, "sentence": "2. The learning procedure is confusing."}, {"text_id": "SylESLC6Fr", "sid": 7, "sentence": "It is highly recommended to provide the pseudocode of the proposed method."}, {"text_id": "SylESLC6Fr", "sid": 8, "sentence": "3. Since there are many tasks and each task has a large-scale data, I'm afraid that the running time will explode. How to deal with this issue?"}], "reviewlabels": [{"text_id": "SylESLC6Fr", "sid": 0, "labels": {"coarse": "Structuring", "fine": "Structuring.Summary", "asp": "", "pol": ""}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "SylESLC6Fr", "sid": 1, "labels": {"coarse": "Structuring", "fine": "Structuring.Summary", "asp": "", "pol": ""}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "SylESLC6Fr", "sid": 2, "labels": {"coarse": "Structuring", "fine": "Structuring.Summary", "asp": "", "pol": ""}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "SylESLC6Fr", "sid": 3, "labels": {"coarse": "Structuring", "fine": "Structuring.Summary", "asp": "", "pol": ""}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "SylESLC6Fr", "sid": 4, "labels": {"coarse": "Structuring", "fine": "Structuring.Heading", "asp": "", "pol": ""}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "SylESLC6Fr", "sid": 5, "labels": {"coarse": "Evaluative", "fine": "Evaluative", "asp": "Motivation/Impact", "pol": "P-Positive"}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "SylESLC6Fr", "sid": 6, "labels": {"coarse": "Evaluative", "fine": "Evaluative", "asp": "Clarity", "pol": "N-Negative"}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "SylESLC6Fr", "sid": 7, "labels": {"coarse": "Request", "fine": "Request.Edit", "asp": "Soundness/Correctness", "pol": "U-Neutral"}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "SylESLC6Fr", "sid": 8, "labels": {"coarse": "Request", "fine": "Request.Explanation", "asp": "Soundness/Correctness", "pol": "U-Neutral"}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}], "rebuttal": [{"text_id": "HkgHcqLVoH", "sid": 0, "sentence": "We would like to thank the reviewer for the positive feedback."}, {"text_id": "HkgHcqLVoH", "sid": 1, "sentence": "We reply to the the two questions below."}, {"text_id": "HkgHcqLVoH", "sid": 2, "sentence": "Q1: The learning procedure is confusing. It is highly recommended to provide the pseudocode of the proposed method."}, {"text_id": "HkgHcqLVoH", "sid": 3, "sentence": "R1: We will provide the pseudocode in the future versions of the paper:"}, {"text_id": "HkgHcqLVoH", "sid": 4, "sentence": "Training:"}, {"text_id": "HkgHcqLVoH", "sid": 5, "sentence": "X_L : clean set"}, {"text_id": "HkgHcqLVoH", "sid": 6, "sentence": "C_L : class set"}, {"text_id": "HkgHcqLVoH", "sid": 7, "sentence": "X_Z : noisy set"}, {"text_id": "HkgHcqLVoH", "sid": 8, "sentence": "# For each class name"}, {"text_id": "HkgHcqLVoH", "sid": 9, "sentence": "For c in C_L:"}, {"text_id": "HkgHcqLVoH", "sid": 10, "sentence": "#Take the clean examples belonging to this class"}, {"text_id": "HkgHcqLVoH", "sid": 11, "sentence": "X_L^c : subset of X_L with label c"}, {"text_id": "HkgHcqLVoH", "sid": 12, "sentence": "#Only consider noisy examples with the class name in the text"}, {"text_id": "HkgHcqLVoH", "sid": 13, "sentence": "X_Z^c = filter_by_text(X_Z)"}, {"text_id": "HkgHcqLVoH", "sid": 14, "sentence": "# Build the graph for this class, and learn the GCN for cleaning"}, {"text_id": "HkgHcqLVoH", "sid": 15, "sentence": "A^c = build_graph(X_Z^c)"}, {"text_id": "HkgHcqLVoH", "sid": 16, "sentence": "M^c = GCN_model(X_L^c, X_Z^c, A^c)"}, {"text_id": "HkgHcqLVoH", "sid": 17, "sentence": "#Clean examples always get weight 1"}, {"text_id": "HkgHcqLVoH", "sid": 18, "sentence": "for i in X_L^c:"}, {"text_id": "HkgHcqLVoH", "sid": 19, "sentence": "r_i = 1.0"}, {"text_id": "HkgHcqLVoH", "sid": 20, "sentence": "#Noisy examples get the learned weight"}, {"text_id": "HkgHcqLVoH", "sid": 21, "sentence": "for i in X_Z^c:"}, {"text_id": "HkgHcqLVoH", "sid": 22, "sentence": "r_i = assign_relevance(M^c(X_Z^c(i))"}, {"text_id": "HkgHcqLVoH", "sid": 23, "sentence": "#Add the noisy examples to the list of training images for this class"}, {"text_id": "HkgHcqLVoH", "sid": 24, "sentence": "X_L^c = concatenate(X_L^c, X_z^c)"}, {"text_id": "HkgHcqLVoH", "sid": 25, "sentence": "#Learn a classifier jointly for all classes."}, {"text_id": "HkgHcqLVoH", "sid": 26, "sentence": "Use the relevance weights for noisy examples when learning the classifier"}, {"text_id": "HkgHcqLVoH", "sid": 27, "sentence": "W = train_classifier(X_L^c, r)"}, {"text_id": "HkgHcqLVoH", "sid": 28, "sentence": "Testing"}, {"text_id": "HkgHcqLVoH", "sid": 29, "sentence": "Given test image Q"}, {"text_id": "HkgHcqLVoH", "sid": 30, "sentence": "v = extract_feature(Q)"}, {"text_id": "HkgHcqLVoH", "sid": 31, "sentence": "scores = W^T v"}, {"text_id": "HkgHcqLVoH", "sid": 32, "sentence": "prediction = argmax(scores)"}, {"text_id": "HkgHcqLVoH", "sid": 33, "sentence": "Q2: Since there are many tasks and each task has a large-scale data, I'm afraid that the running time will explode. How to deal with this issue?"}, {"text_id": "HkgHcqLVoH", "sid": 34, "sentence": "R2: The complexity is linear in the number of classes, since classes are processed independently."}, {"text_id": "HkgHcqLVoH", "sid": 35, "sentence": "Furthermore, text filtering is applied before cleaning, which reduces the number of images to be considered for a given class."}, {"text_id": "HkgHcqLVoH", "sid": 36, "sentence": "Please also see the response R1 to reviewer1."}], "rebuttallabels": [{"labels": {"alignments": [], "responsetype": "social", "coarseresponse": "nonarg"}, "text_id": "HkgHcqLVoH", "sid": 0}, {"labels": {"alignments": [], "responsetype": "structuring", "coarseresponse": "nonarg"}, "text_id": "HkgHcqLVoH", "sid": 1}, {"labels": {"alignments": [6, 7], "responsetype": "structuring", "coarseresponse": "nonarg"}, "text_id": "HkgHcqLVoH", "sid": 2}, {"labels": {"alignments": [6, 7], "responsetype": "by-cr_manu_Yes", "coarseresponse": "concur"}, "text_id": "HkgHcqLVoH", "sid": 3}, {"labels": {"alignments": [6, 7], "responsetype": "answer", "coarseresponse": "concur"}, "text_id": "HkgHcqLVoH", "sid": 4}, {"labels": {"alignments": [6, 7], "responsetype": "answer", "coarseresponse": "concur"}, "text_id": "HkgHcqLVoH", "sid": 5}, {"labels": {"alignments": [6, 7], "responsetype": "answer", "coarseresponse": "concur"}, "text_id": "HkgHcqLVoH", "sid": 6}, {"labels": {"alignments": [6, 7], "responsetype": "answer", "coarseresponse": "concur"}, "text_id": "HkgHcqLVoH", "sid": 7}, {"labels": {"alignments": [6, 7], "responsetype": "answer", "coarseresponse": "concur"}, "text_id": "HkgHcqLVoH", "sid": 8}, {"labels": {"alignments": [6, 7], "responsetype": "answer", "coarseresponse": "concur"}, "text_id": "HkgHcqLVoH", "sid": 9}, {"labels": {"alignments": [6, 7], "responsetype